    <div id="index-banner" class="parallax-container">
      <div class="section no-pad-bot">
        <div class="container">
          <br><br>
          <h1 class="header center teal-text text-lighten-2"><%= title %></h1>
          <div class="row center">
            <h5 class="header col s12 light" style="color:white">Our Home Planet</h5>
          </div>
          <br>
          <br>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="parallax"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/97/The_Earth_seen_from_Apollo_17.jpg" alt="Earth img 1" style="width:100%"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
            <h4>Earth</h4>
            <p class="flow-text left-align light">Earth is the third planet from the Sun and the only object in the Universe known to harbor life. It is the densest planet in the Solar System and the largest of the four terrestrial planets.
            <br>
            <br>
According to radiometric dating and other sources of evidence, Earth formed about 4.54 billion years ago. Earth's gravity interacts with other objects in space, especially the Sun and the Moon, Earth's only natural satellite. Earth's axis of rotation is tilted, producing seasonal variations on the planet's surface. The gravitational interaction between the Earth and Moon causes ocean tides, stabilizes the Earth's orientation on its axis, and gradually slows its rotation.
<br>
<br>
About 71% of Earth's surface is covered with water, mostly by its oceans. The remaining 29% is land. Earth's interior remains active with a solid iron inner core, a liquid outer core that generates the Earth's magnetic field, and a convecting mantle that drives plate tectonics.<br>
            <br>
            <div>Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth</div>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="parallax-container valign-wrapper">
      <div class="section no-pad-bot">
        <div class="container">
          <h4 style="color:white">Earth: Stats</h4>
          <div class="row center">
            <h5 class="header col s12 light" style="color:white"></h5>
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="parallax"><img src="https://images-assets.nasa.gov/image/as11-44-6549/as11-44-6549~orig.jpg" alt="Earth img 2" style="width:100%"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m6">
            <p class="flow-text left-align light">
              Earth orbits 150 million kilometers from the Sun.
              <br>
              At our Manhattan scale, Earth is 495.88 meters away from The Sphere (about five football fields).
              <br>
              In our journey across Manhattan, this puts us on Broadway near Exchange Place, in the Canyon of Heroes.
              <br>
              Earth would be about 4.1cm in size at this scale.
              <br>
              Our moon is about 1/3 the diameter of Earth, and orbits at a distance of 239,000 miles, about 10 earth diameters.
              <br>
              The moon would be about 1.3cm in size at this scale, orbiting our Manhattan Earth at a distance of 40cm.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div  class="col s12 m6 materialboxed" data-caption="Relative orbit of Earth from The Sphere">

              <img src="/images/Earth_orbit.png" alt="Raduis of Earth's orbit at scale" style="width:100%">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="position:relative;height:400px;width:80%;margin:0 auto">

      <iframe width="100%" height="400"
        src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/streetview?key=<%= process.env.GOOGLE_KEY %>&location=40.7067316,-74.0125597&heading=45&pitch=5&fov=100">
      </iframe>

      <div style="width:900px;height:400px;z-index:2;position:absolute;top:0px">
        <a-scene embedded style="left:250;height:300;width:400">
          <a-sphere position="0 1.8 -1" radius=".01" color="#727ba3"></a-sphere>
        </a-scene>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="container section no-pad-bot">
      <p style="text-align:center">Earth is the blue planet, 4cm in size, orbiting in the trees above Broadway in the Financial District. (Use arrow keys / mouse to pan / zoom)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <p class="flow-text light">Onward to the Red Planet.
            </p>
            <div class="row center">
              <a href="/mars" class="btn-large waves-effect waves-light teal lighten-1">Next: MARS</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
